[if ending-agreed-with-justinian-premise is false]In another life, perhaps, things could be different. But it's all in the past now. All I can do now is try my best to save lives. To live up to the promise that I made to my father... to Doctor Cavala... to myself[otherwise]Perhaps you were right, Justinian. In the end, I took the easy way out, just as you did. I couldn't escape the circle of life and death. But I told you, on that day, that until I lost every ounce of hope I would continue to fight.

