	otherwise if Walked Away Ending is happening:
		say "How long will I keep doing this?

In a way, I only have myself to blame. I've always had the key to saving the district in the palm of my hand. If the Vigiles knew what I knew, if they saw in Justinian what I saw, so many lives would be saved -- but I can't bring myself to tell them. I can't incriminate him. I keep clinging to the hope that he can be saved, that my choice won't have been in vain.

Perhaps I really am an idiot. He certainly thinks I am. [if ending-agreed-with-justinian-premise is false]It takes a special kind of idiot to cling to an ideal to the point of hurting others... to condemn so many because I couldn't end the life of someone I cared about. Is it dumb to hope? To listen to your heart and believe that your faith will be rewarded[otherwise]It takes a special kind of idiot to see the world as it is and believe that things can be different... that you can save the world without ending the life of someone you care about. But what if I wasn't? What if there's still kindness left in his heart -- still hope left in this corpse of a city[end if]?

I want to believe. I really do. Primes forgive me.

[if ending-agreed-with-justinian-premise is false]In another life, perhaps, things could be different. But it's all in the past now. All I can do now is try my best to minimize the harm that Justinian does in the world. I have to live up to the promise that I made to my father... to Doctor Cavala... to myself[otherwise]Perhaps you were right, Justinian. In the end, I was the same as all the others. I didn't have it in me to take the final step. But I told you, on that day, that until I lost every ounce of hope I would continue to fight.

I'm still fighting, Justinian. I owe you that much[end if]. ";
	otherwise if Usurper Ending is happening:
		say "I thought about Justinian again today.

It's funny... when I picture his face, I still feel that flush. That shyness. That heartbreak. I feel like I'm seventeen years old all over again, and Justinian is showing me how to live. I thought I was over him, but evidently I haven't moved on as much as I'd imagined. 

In many ways, Justinian was a visionary. He showed me that there was a better way to do good. He showed me that we should not treat the symptoms but the cause. In my one year as a Doctor, I have achieved more than Cavala could ever have dreamed of.

It's such a pity that he was blinded by his flaws. He was sloppy. Too passionate. He ended up harming the district more than he helped it. And for someone like Justinian -- someone who thinks himself above the law, and justified in causing whatever suffering he wishes -- there was only one fate, regardless of my personal feelings for him.

A city can only have one magistrate, Justinian. I saw that in the Channelworks control tower all those months ago. Perhaps if you'd seen that too, and repented, you would still be by my side. ";
	otherwise if Collaborator Ending is happening:
		say "I'd always dreamed of being part of something like this, but I never imagined that it would be so real... so immediate. Great changes are already happening, and I look forward to more with a kind of breathless anticipation.

It's intoxicating to be on the cusp of a new age. To sit and work knowing that the future is just at hand. ";
		
